---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy of Avorix GmbH — information on the processing of your personal data in accordance with GDPR.">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-avorix-dark mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">1. Privacy at a Glance</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-6 mb-2">General Information</h3>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        The following information provides a simple overview of what happens to your personal data
        when you visit this website. Personal data is any data that can be used to personally identify you.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-6 mb-2">Data Collection on This Website</h3>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        <strong>Who is responsible for data collection on this website?</strong><br />
        Data processing on this website is carried out by the website operator:<br /><br />
        AVORIX GmbH<br />
        Fallenbrunnen 14<br />
        88045 Friedrichshafen, Germany<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:info@avorix.de" class="text-avorix-dark hover:underline">info@avorix.de</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">2. Hosting</h2>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        This website is hosted by an external service provider. Personal data collected on this website
        is stored on the host's servers. This may include IP addresses, contact requests, meta and
        communication data, contract data, contact details, names, website access, and other data
        generated through a website.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        Our host is:<br />
        Hostinger International Ltd.<br />
        61 Lordou Vironos Street, 6023 Larnaca, Cyprus
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">3. General Information and Mandatory Disclosures</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-6 mb-2">Data Protection</h3>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        The operators of these pages take the protection of your personal data very seriously.
        We treat your personal data confidentially and in accordance with statutory data protection
        regulations and this privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-6 mb-2">Responsible Entity</h3>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        The responsible entity for data processing on this website is:<br /><br />
        AVORIX GmbH<br />
        Managing Director: B&ouml;rge Penk<br />
        Email: info@avorix.de
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">4. Data Collection on This Website</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-6 mb-2">Server Log Files</h3>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        The website provider automatically collects and stores information in server log files
        that your browser automatically transmits. These are:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-avorix-gray list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-2">
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Operating system used</li>
        <li>Referrer URL</li>
        <li>Host name of the accessing computer</li>
        <li>Time of the server request</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        This data is not combined with other data sources. The basis for data processing
        is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-6 mb-2">Contact Form</h3>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        If you send us inquiries via the contact form, your details from the inquiry form,
        including the contact data you provided, will be stored for the purpose of processing
        the inquiry and for follow-up questions. We will not share this data without your consent.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">5. Technically Necessary Local Storage</h2>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        Your consent choice is stored as a technically necessary entry in your browser's local storage (<code>localStorage</code>) under the key <code>avorix_consent</code>. No data is transferred to third parties through this entry. The entry remains in your browser until you withdraw your consent, delete your browser data, or a technical renewal of the consent request occurs.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        This website does not set any analytics or marketing cookies by default. The only currently optional category is "Statistics". Analytics services are only loaded if you consent to the Statistics category via our cookie banner. Currently, no Google Ads, remarketing, or other marketing tags are used.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">7. Google Tag Manager and Google Analytics 4</h2>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        When you consent to the Statistics category, we use Google Tag Manager and Google Analytics 4 provided by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Your consent under Art.&nbsp;6(1)(a) GDPR. Access to or storage of information on your device is based, where required, on your consent under Section&nbsp;25(1) TDDDG.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Statistical reach and usage analysis. We use Google Analytics 4 to understand how our website is used and which content is helpful to visitors.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Data processed:</strong> Technical usage data, device information, event data and pseudonymous online identifiers may be processed.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>IP processing:</strong> According to Google, IP address data from users in the EU is used to derive approximate location information and is then deleted without being logged in Google Analytics.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Recipient:</strong> Google Ireland Limited. Processing outside the European Economic Area (EEA) may occur. The transfer to third countries is based on Standard Contractual Clauses adopted by the European Commission (Art.&nbsp;46(2)(c) GDPR) and additionally on the adequacy decision of the European Commission for the USA (EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework).
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Storage duration:</strong> GA4 cookies (<code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code>) remain in the browser for up to 2 years under the currently used standard configuration. Event data is retained in the Avorix GA4 property for 14 months.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Google Consent Mode v2:</strong> We use Google Consent Mode v2 in Basic Mode. Without your consent, no cookies are set and no data is transferred to Google. The GTM script is only loaded after consent.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        <strong>Withdrawal:</strong> You can withdraw your consent at any time via the "Cookie settings" link in the footer. The withdrawal applies for the future; data already transmitted is not retroactively deleted.
      </p>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray mt-3">
        We have concluded a data processing agreement with Google.
        Further information: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-avorix-dark hover:underline">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-avorix-dark mt-8 mb-3">8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-avorix-gray">
        You have the right at any time to free information about your stored personal data,
        its origin and recipients, and the purpose of data processing, as well as a right to
        correction, blocking, or deletion of this data. You can contact us at any time regarding
        this and other questions about personal data.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
